title: Israel's Benjamin Netanyahu criticises anti-government protesters in televised statement
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has given a televised statement criticising anti-government protesters after the previous defence minister and senior opposition figure Benny Gantz warned that the country was heading for civil war.

title: Everything we know so far after dozens killed in Greece train crash
description: More than 36 people have been killed in a fatal train collision in Greece, as questions remain over its cause.

title: Size of operation to bury Turkey's quake dead 'staggering' - with tens of thousands feared still missing
description: We knew the name of the village with the location pinpointed on our mobile phones, but we did not need a map to find a place called Kapicam.

title: Israeli minister says Palestinian town targeted by rioters should be 'wiped out'
description: Israel's finance minister has said that the West Bank town of Huwara should be "wiped out".

title: Bird flu victim had virus with mutations that made it better adapted to human cells
description: The bird flu virus isolated from a girl who died from the disease had mutations that made it better adapted to human cells, Sky News has learned.

title: 'My spiritual girlfriend': Mummy discovered in delivery driver's bag
description: A mummy was found in a man's cooler bag in Peru when police stopped and searched him for drinking alcohol at a cultural site.

title: French football legend and World Cup record holder dies
description: Just Fontaine, the French footballing great who scored an "incredible" record 13 goals at the 1958 World Cup, has died at the age of 89.

title: Greta Thunberg twice detained by police at anti-wind farm protest
description: Greta Thunberg has been twice detained at protests in Oslo over an onshore wind farm which she and activists say hinders the rights of the Sami indigenous people to raise reindeer in Arctic Norway.

title: Finland starts construction of Russia border fence as lawmakers give final approval for NATO bid
description: Finland has started building a fence along parts of its 1,340km (832-mile) border with Russia amid security tensions with its neighbour over the Ukraine war.

title: Man who survived on ketchup for 24 days at sea to get new boat - from Heinz
description: A man who spent 24 days lost at sea seemed to be missing again - but he has been tracked down after a massive social media hunt instigated by Heinz.

title: Denmark to scrap public holiday to pay for NATO spending
description: Denmark has scrapped a public holiday in order to help pay for its NATO defence spending commitments.

title: China lab leak 'most likely' caused COVID outbreak, FBI director says
description: The director of the FBI has said the agency believes COVID-19 "most likely" came from a lab leak in China.

title: Bola Tinubu is declared winner of Nigeria's presidential election but rivals call for a re-vote
description: Bola Tinubu has been declared the winner of Nigeria's presidential election, despite early demands from rivals for a re-vote.

title: At least 16 people killed after passenger train and freight train collide in Greece
description: At least 16 people are reported to have been killed and dozens injured after two trains collided in Greece.

title: At least 26 people killed after passenger train and freight train collide in Greece
description: At least 26 people are reported to have been killed and dozens injured after two trains collided in Greece.
